body:
I was talking about what we do before the test. The test cleanup after execution is fine for the default case.

I think we shouldn't block the test creation on different paths. Be forced to place the test only inside the temp directory doesn't seems so useful to me.
What if we make the `-testdatadir` arg the base path for all test cases, and create a subdirectory for each run test inside it?. (with this, you would not need to delete the datadir at the beginning, because it will not exist).
E.g.
```c++
fs::path base_dir;
if (!m_node.args->IsArgSet("-testdatadir")) {
    base_dir = fs::temp_directory_path();
} else {
    std::string testdatadir = m_node.args->GetArg("-testdatadir").value();
    // Allow only a simple string (a single path component) because we're
    // going to remove this path, and it would be bad if it was "../../home".
    if (testdatadir.find(fs::path::preferred_separator) != std::string::npos) {
        std::cerr << "-testdatadir cannot contain path separators: " << testdatadir << std::endl;
        exit(1);
    }

    // Allow only regular directory paths
    if (fs::is_regular_file(testdatadir) || fs::is_symlink(testdatadir)) {
        std::cerr << "-testdatadir needs to be a directory path: " << testdatadir << std::endl;
        exit(1);
    }

    // Create base dir if needed
    fs::create_directories(testdatadir);
    base_dir = fs::path{testdatadir.c_str()};
    m_has_custom_datadir = true;
}

// Create test dir within the base directory
m_path_root = base_dir / "test_common_" PACKAGE_NAME / g_insecure_rand_ctx_temp_path.rand256().ToString().c_str();
```

